<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-12-16T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-12-16T20:00:00-05:00" n="403" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d403">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/14504: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-12-16T20:00:00-05:00">December 16, 1938—8
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>422. Your 787, December 16, 3 p.m., paragraph 2. In the contingency
                                mentioned, the Department desires that you continue to maintain <pb facs="0425" n="421" xml:id="pg_421"/> the position of this
                                Government as expressed to the Japanese Government both in writing
                                and orally.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>